This paper deals with the training of capsule networks, which are a type of neural network architecture. The paper specifically focuses on the use of dynamic routing, which is a technique used to pass information between capsules in the network. This makes the paper most likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with image generation, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised learning, which is a topic that falls under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper's focus on capsule networks and their routing schemes suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of an energy function to model the network suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
